  "handoff_packets": [
    {
      "content": "{\n  \"cwd\": \"/Users/sam.zhang/Documents/codex-supervisor\",\n  \"execution_layer_policy\": {\n    \"agentic_lead_policy\": {\n      \"min_subagents\": 0,\n      \"policy\": \"off\",\n      \"required_evidence_grade\": \"self_reported\",\n      \"required_roles\": [],\n      \"solo_exception_for_artifact_only_gates\": false\n    },\n    \"allowed_dynamic_workflow_task_classes\": [],\n    \"codex_supervises_final_artifact\": true,\n    \"dynamic_workflow_task_class\": null,\n    \"lead_execution_layer\": \"single_lead_worker\",\n    \"mode\": \"lead_direct\",\n    \"preview_required_gates\": [],\n    \"supervision_layer\": \"codex_plus_lead\"\n  },\n  \"expected_decisions\": [],\n  \"expected_objections\": [],\n  \"expected_specialists\": [],\n  \"gate\": \"outcome_review\",\n  \"instruction\": \"Supervisor-owned workflow gate: outcome_review.\\n\\nIntent:\\nBuild a REVIEWER-PANEL eval runner that measures reviewer agreement/disagreement, failure overlap, correlation, cost, latency, false-accepts, and false-blocks across the panel on a labeled task set - the data substrate REQUIRED before any calibrated weighting. This is DISTINCT from the lead-mode/fan-out eval (separate later track).\\n\\nEXACT FACTS: supervisor/agentic_eval.py has build_agentic_eval_report(rows) - a report aggregator, NOT a runner; it does not execute reviewers or measure their dependency.\\n\\nSCOPE (do):\\n1. A runner that replays a labeled set of gate decisions through the panel (slice 1-3) and records each reviewer's verdict.\\n2. Emit per-reviewer + PAIRWISE metrics: agreement rate, failure overlap / correlation, false-accept, false-block, cost, latency.\\n3. Deterministic + replayable (cassettes/fixtures); reports only - does NOT change the gate or aggregation, does NOT flip any policy.\\n\\nNON-GOALS: NOT the lead-mode/fan-out eval (separate); do NOT alter the gate/aggregation; do NOT introduce weighting here (this only MEASURES the inputs to it).\\n\\nACCEPTANCE:\\n- The runner executes the panel over the labeled set and emits per-reviewer + pairwise dependency metrics (agreement, correlation/failure-overlap, false-accept/false-block, cost, latency).\\n- The report makes reviewer independence/correlation legible (the input calibrated weighting will consume).\\n- Deterministic replay; full suite green; ledger + replay artifacts exported.\\n\\nReview this gate against the current source artifacts and return a typed dual_agent_outcome.\\nUse decisions/objections to say whether the gate should accept, revise, or deny.\",\n  \"lead_skill\": null,\n  \"outcome_validation_policy\": {\n    \"fidelity_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"malformed_outcome\": \"retry_once_with_corrective_packet\",\n    \"subprocess_failure\": \"abort_to_operator\",\n    \"timeout\": \"abort_to_operator\"\n  },\n  \"packet_schema_version\": \"dual-agent-handoff/v1\",\n  \"planning_artifacts\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"prd\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-eval-runner-20260601/source/prd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"e6b6c82803869dbe34e83cbc3d6b3455ae9a3447aec5794b30fd6db5d98b7bd4\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"grill_findings\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-eval-runner-20260601/source/grill-findings.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"9abf58a0d5b165f27c3892dff2d7ace55fba421be9fa259de60eb9f79a335420\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"issues\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-eval-runner-20260601/source/issues.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"dcb47cd458d114db531f33a846fa70509a9ab6ae3a2e5ffa7eb7421dcf246514\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"tdd_plan\",\n      \"mutable_by_worker\": false,\n      \"path\": \"docs/dual-agent/reviewer-panel-eval-runner-20260601/source/tdd.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"ad235cd4867e82ca48eab70e363038ac49643f44ad78c27e0a70cab05b74b92d\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"gril